# [upstream-candidate][security] Scrub credential patterns from tool results
#
# Before the model sees a tool result, run it through a credential-pattern
# redactor. This is defense-in-depth: secrets should not be in tool
# results in the first place (see SECURITY.md §2.4), but realistic tools
# leak them anyway — `cat .env`, `env`, `git config --list`, misconfigured
# curl verbose, container inspect, etc.
#
# Pattern set is derived from the Genie hermes-agent redactor
# (/Users/gtrush/Downloads/genie-2.0/engines/hermes-agent/tools/mcp_tool.py
# :: _CREDENTIAL_PATTERN) and extended with:
#   - Anthropic sk-ant-*
#   - OpenRouter sk-or-*
#   - Stripe sk_live_* / rk_live_*
#   - AWS AKIA*
#   - Google AIza*
#   - GitHub ghp_/gho_/ghs_/github_pat_
#   - JWT three-segment base64url with eyJ prefix
#   - Bearer tokens
#   - .env-style lines for sensitive key names
#
# Matches become "[REDACTED:<kind>]" so the model can still reason about
# the *presence* of a value without learning it.
#
# Jellyclaw ticket: SEC-004
# Line numbers approximate against @sst/opencode@1.1.10.
# --------------------------------------------------------------------

diff --git a/packages/opencode/src/tool/result.ts b/packages/opencode/src/tool/result.ts
